Quick Guide

  Basic steps to enable virtual texturing in your scene:
    
    1. Create an AT Manager object using the following main menu option: 
	   "GameObject/Create Other/AmplifyTexture Manager"
      
    2. Add your Camera(s) to the Manager's "Cameras" list. This way, an 
	   AT Runtime component will be added automatically to your existing camera(s).
		   
         OR

       Create an AT Camera object using the following main menu option: 
	   "GameObject/Create Other/AmplifyTexture Camera"
      
    3. Create a Virtual Texture using the Asset creation menu in your 
	   Project tab: "Create/Virtual Texture". A new asset should appear 
	   under the current folder as: "New Virtual Texture"
      
    4. Add your Virtual Texture(s) to the Manager's "Virtual Textures" list.
         
    5. You are now ready to start assigning Amplify Texture compatible shaders to
       your materials. As you do this, the VT build system will automatically detect 
	   the new compatible materials and incrementally add their textures to the VT.
         
       The virtual texture will be resized automatically to fit new textures.

       You can also use the converter in "Window/Amplify Texture/Tools", to 
	   serial convert all compatible materials into their respective Amplify 
	   replacements. Reversing this operation is also possible using the same tool.
         
    6. Just press Play and take it for a spin.
	
